      "writtenOn": "2020-11-03T01:32:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, and I considered measuring the latency, but didn\u0027t.\n\nThe numbers will tell us the upload performance but it won\u0027t tell us how much delay it added to the total execution time. Even if uploads were slow at a time, it could be covered up if # of artifacts were small, compared # of test results. artifactDrainDuration will tell us how much delay added to the total execution time due to slow artifact uploads.\n\nEven if we wanted to instrument the performance of artifact uploads, we would want to track the performance for each of the file-size buckets. Otherwise, we would track the upload performance of big and small artifacts together, and we can possibly experience red-herring from flaky-tests if certain test failures produce large artifacts. Also, we would want percentile, and possibly a moving window.\n\nIn short, if we wanted to find how much artifact uploads slowed a given test run, measuring the execution of artifact channel draining is sufficient and more accurate.\nIf we wanted to monitor the performance of artifact uploads, we\u0027d probably want tsmon or something similar.",
      "parentUuid": "7f40fd7f_432d0a0f",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 71,
        "startChar": 0,
