      "writtenOn": "2020-11-03T01:32:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "As I mentioned in another comment, I was afraid that the field defs of sinkStats{} were biased to the usage of rdb-stream only. Of course, the field def of shutdownDuration would probably remain the same, but those stat fields for request latencies would not.\n\nThus, I moved the implementations of the storage to cli/sink_stats.go, but kept this sink package agnostic to the detail storage implementation.",
      "parentUuid": "9845b398_d23fe8b1",
      "revId": "9b99e6253aa43d628a4291ce1ef0155272ede7af",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
