      "writtenOn": "2020-11-04T02:48:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m not sure if we are on the same page.\n\nIIUC, you are suggesting to report # of pending items, instead of the time elapsed. Logging # of pending items won\u0027t tell us how much delay ReportTestResults added. # of pending items won\u0027t give us how soon ReportTestResults() will start adding delays, either.\n\nIf a queue was saturated, the goroutine would be blocked in L171 or L173. If it was unblocked, the queue is no longer saturated. When this function logs # of pending items on exit, the number is probably smaller than the max allowed items of the queue. # of pending items on the queue won\u0027t tell us how much delay was added in the particular ReportTestResults() session.\n\nPlease LMK if I totally missed your point.",
      "parentUuid": "ee5146cb_e7a7135a",
